# Project: tauri-kit — Cross-platform Video/Audio Conference App
## Stack
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite (inside Tauri)
- Backend (Tauri): Rust (src-tauri/)
- Token server: Node.js + TypeScript (server/)
- Media: LiveKit (self-hosted SFU)
- Agent (OPTIONAL): Python
  STT: faster-whisper-server (model: tiny)
  Summary: Ollama qwen2.5:0.5b
  Enabled via ENABLE_STT=true / ENABLE_SUMMARY=true in agent/.env

## Architecture modules
- src/           → React frontend (components, hooks, pages, services)
- src-tauri/     → Rust Tauri commands (IPC, file save)
- server/        → Token server (JWT, room lifecycle)
- agent/         → OPTIONAL Python LiveKit Agent
- docs/          → README, ARCHITECTURE, TESTING, AI_GUIDELINES
- .github/       → CI workflow

## Principles (SOLID, Modular)
- Each module has single responsibility
- No business logic in UI components
- All Tauri commands typed, all errors handled
- Never store user data or session history server-side
- Tokens: one-time use, TTL 1h, destroyed after session
- STT/summary: fully opt-in, graceful degradation if agent absent

## Commit style: feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:, test:, refactor:

## Security (HIGH RISK ZONES)
- Tokens: short TTL, no reuse, no server-side storage
- E2EE: LiveKit ExternalE2EEKeyProvider, key never logged or sent via server
- No API keys/secrets in source — only .env files
- All .env in .gitignore

## Before declaring done: pnpm build && pnpm lint && tests pass